data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: 1. Symbol files containing quote information are displayed here. Highlight files (symbols) you wish to update. If none appear, click "Get historical quotes" radio button (2), add symbol(s) to download in the text box (5), set the From and To dates (6), and click Start (7). That will build quote files using one of the quote providers shown in 3.

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value: Use this form to update quote information. Below is an explanation of each control. WARNING: Use this form well after the close (about 4 hours for yahoo) otherwise new information may be unavailable. The Update Form will appear similar to that shown.

data.name: Label4.Text
data.value: 3. Select the quote provider of your choice. The Quotes/min numeric control is for Alpha Vantage users. Enter the maximum number of symbols per minute their service can handle. Click the ? button for more information.

data.name: Label9.Text
data.value: 7. "Update All Portfolios" allows the program to update all files in each of your portfolios. "Browse" selects the location of the symbol files shown in 1. "Stop" halts a download. "Start" begins a download. "Select All" highlights all files shown in 1. "Help" calls this form, and "Done" returns you to the Main Form.
